'''''ten-''''', meaning "arrive", is a scrapped [[Quenya]] verb. Tolkien subsequently emended ''ten-'' and its gloss were struck out, and was changed to ''men-'' in all the other derivatives.<ref name=VT49>{{VT|49a}}, p. 23</ref>
==Other forms==
*''tene'' (aorist: "comes, arrives, is with us")
*''etēnie'' (perfect: "has just arrived")
*''tenuva'' (future: "will arrive")
==Etymology==
*Root [[TEN]]<ref name=VT49/>
==See also==
*''[[Tûl]]'' (a definitive word for "come, arrive")
*''[[tenna]]''
